name: Suomenlinna Church
description: This swedish designed architecture, It is one of the oldest shrines in Helsinki. It greets those those arriving from the sea by transmitting the H code with its Gustavian style tower, to indicate Helsinki.

name: Seurasaari Island and Open-Air Museum
description: To get a unique hands-on experience of rural life in the Finnish countryside, the Suerasaari Open-Air museum is the place to go. Its highlights are Traditional rural Finland,Open-air museum, Cottages, Farmsteads and manors.

name: Sea Fortress Suomenlinna
description: This fort which was biult in 18th Century was  designated as UNESCO World Heritage Site.Suomenlinna consists of several defensive and utilitarian buildings that blend the architecture and functionality of the fortress within the surrounding landscape.

name: kaisaniemi botanical garden
description: It is the subordinate of Finnish Musume of Natural History of Helsinki University. This park is used for research and teaching.The visitor can see not only the world's biggest seed, but also an impressive collection of orchids

name: Helsinki Winter Garden
description: This garden is famous for the collection of winter plant. There is over 200 different planet inside the winter house. There are three rooms in house i.e. palm room, wastern wing and cactus room

name: Didrichsen Art Museum
description: This museum was founded by finnish architecture Viljo Revell.It is located at Kuusisaari. This musume was built in two phase.
